rapid climate change, collisions with asteroids or comets, pandemics, and financial crashes. Florin Diacu tells the harrowing true stories of people impacted by these terrible events, and of the scientists racing against time to predict when the next big disaster will strike. He describes the mathematical models that are so critical to understanding the laws of nature and foretelling potentially lethal phenomena, the history of modeling and its prospects for success in the future, and the enormous challenges to scientific prediction posed by the chaos phenomenon, which is the high instability that underlies many processes around us. Yielding new insights into the perils that can touch every one of us, Megadisasters shows how the science of predicting disasters holds the promise of a safer and brighter tomorrow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aBIOGRAPHY &ampxAUTOBIOGRAPHYvAdventurers &ampxExplorers. 0aBIOGRAPHY and ampxAUTOBIOGRAPHYvAdventurers and ampxExplorers. 0aClimatic changesvSocial aspects. 0aClimatic changesxSocial aspects. 0aHISTORYvExpeditions &ampxDiscoveries. 0aHistoryvExpeditions and ampxDiscoveries. 0aHuman beingsvEffect of climate on. 0aHuman beingsxEffect of climate on. 0aNATUREvNatural Disasters. 0aNatural disastersvForecasting. 0aNatural disastersxForecasting. 0aNaturevNatural Disasters. 0aSOCIAL SCIENCEvDisasters &ampxDisaster Relief. 0aSocial sciencesvDisasters and ampxDisaster Relief. 0aTRAVELvSpecial InterestvAdventure. 0aTravelvSpecial InterestvAdventure. 7aNATURE / Natural Disasters.2bisacsh  a1918 flu pandemic.  a1980 eruption of Mount St. Helens.  a2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami.  aA Brief History of Time.  aAircraft.  aAstronomer.  aAstronomy.  aAvian influenza.  aBiologist.  aCalculation.  aCarbon dioxid